05/09/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Unsettled debts between the killer and one of the victims were behind Thursday's triple murder in Skopje, Interior Minister Gordana Jankulovska announced on Friday (September 3rd).
She said that the alleged killer has surrendered to police and explained his motive.
The assailant allegedly admits he targeted one of the victims, who had a criminal record for drug trafficking.
Jankulovska confirmed that one victim was an employee of the ministry but said she has no information about his relation to the other victims.
The incident happened late Thursday in a Skopje restaurant.
(MIA, Makfax, A1, Alsat M, Sitel - 03/09/10)
